-- Gamesa to Supply 230 Megawatts of Turbines for India Wind Farms
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-05-23T17:49:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-23/gamesa-to-supply-230-megawatts-of-turbines-for-india-wind-farms.html
Gamesa Corp. Tecnologica SA (GAM) , Spain’s
largest wind-turbine maker, agreed to supply 230 megawatts of
gear to two companies building power plants in India.  Gamesa is providing 65 of its 2-megawatt turbines to CLP
Holdings Ltd.’s China Light & Power India unit and will maintain
them for 10 years, the Zamudio, Spain-based company said in a
 statement  today.  The company will also deliver 100 megawatts of turbines to
 Greenko Group Plc (GKO) , and the deal may be expanded by an additional
200 megawatts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Justin Doom in  New York  at 
 jdoom1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
